  "body": "Unsanitized input from a command line argument flows into extractall, where it is used to extract files from a tar archive. This may result files outside destination directory to be overwritten, resulting in an arbitrary file write.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/execution-specs/blob/5e8a9c33b4fa607cac58e1a92e186c1ef4f0230a/scripts/download_geth_linux.py#L31\r\n\r\n## Data flow :\r\n### 10 steps in 1 file\r\n`scripts/download_geth_linux.py`\r\n\r\n16:12 `parser.parse_argsparser.parse_args` (SOURCE)\r\n1 - 2 `parser.parse_args` (SOURCE)\r\n1\r\n`parser.parse_args`\r\n2\r\n`args`\r\n3\r\n`argsargs.dir`\r\n4 - 5\r\n`args`\r\n4\r\n`args.dir`\r\n5\r\n`dir: str`\r\n6\r\n`dir`\r\n7\r\n`dir`\r\n8\r\n`dirgeth_tar.extractall`\r\n9 - 10\r\n`dir`\r\n9\r\n`geth_tar.extractall`",
